<div id="review_3415939686" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3415939686" />
    <a title="Caidyn (he/him/his)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his"><img alt="Caidyn (he/him/his)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532186157p2/13614926.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3415939686?book_show_action=true">Jul 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Caidyn (he/him/his)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Caidyn (he/him/his)" href="/user/show/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his">Caidyn (he/him/his)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his?shelf=young-adult-fiction">young-adult-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13614926-caidyn-he-him-his?shelf=arc">arc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3415939686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13561414791131775157"><i>I received an ARC through Netgalley in exchange for an honest review!</i><br/><br/><b>CW: child abuse, physical abuse, intimate partner violence, rape of multiple kinds, murder, serial killer, and general themes of violence<br/><br/>3.5/5</b><br/><br/>Laure is on my radar for sure. I didn&apos;t know what to expect from this book, but it was excellent. One that I&apos;m definitely going to reread at some point.<br/><br/>So, this book is about Mayhem and her family. She and her mother, Roxy, fled from their home to get away from Lyle, the abusive stepfathe</span>
  <span id="freeText13561414791131775157" style="display:none"><i>I received an ARC through Netgalley in exchange for an honest review!</i><br /><br /><b>CW: child abuse, physical abuse, intimate partner violence, rape of multiple kinds, murder, serial killer, and general themes of violence<br /><br />3.5/5</b><br /><br />Laure is on my radar for sure. I didn't know what to expect from this book, but it was excellent. One that I'm definitely going to reread at some point.<br /><br />So, this book is about Mayhem and her family. She and her mother, Roxy, fled from their home to get away from Lyle, the abusive stepfather. They went to Roxy's sister for shelter and a place to stay for a while. Except, the Brayburns rule this town in some ways and Mayhem has a lot to learn about her family history.<br /><br />It's told in alternating perspectives. The main one is Mayhem and her journey to find out about her family history and more about herself. Then there's also diary entries where we find out more about the Brayburn history.<br /><br />Not only is there the family healing between Roxy and Mayhem, but there's also a serial killer in the new town that the Brayburns can find and help save. I really liked this plot, but I found the family history more interesting than the other aspects of the plot. Also, and I'll be honest here, I was very stressed while reading this book so I didn't absorb as much information as I would have liked. Which is why this is a book I want to reread at some point so I can see it bump up to a full 4 stars or more!<br /><br />Overall, a really fantastic book that sucked me in.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13561414791131775157" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


