<div id="review_3643266348" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3643266348" />
    <a title="Nursebookie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/98423937-nursebookie"><img alt="Nursebookie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1605822081p2/98423937.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3643266348?book_show_action=true">Nov 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nursebookie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nursebookie" href="/user/show/98423937-nursebookie">Nursebookie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781250297938" href="/book/show/51171648-mayhem">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/98423937-nursebookie?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/98423937-nursebookie?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/98423937-nursebookie?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/98423937-nursebookie?shelf=supernatural">supernatural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/98423937-nursebookie?shelf=wednesdaybooks">wednesdaybooks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3643266348" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5777268709366640474">Mayhem<br/>By Estelle Laure<br/><br/>There is nothing more I love to read about than stories set in the 80’s and in my home state of California. The story has elements of magical realism, witches, a thrilling murder mystery and supernatural – which I enjoyed reading about. The story flowed well and written in a very distinct voice that I really enjoyed including diary entries. The story is about Mayhem Brayburn and her mother Roxy who leaves to Santa Maria, California, a beautiful coastal town to escape an abu</span>
  <span id="freeText5777268709366640474" style="display:none">Mayhem<br />By Estelle Laure<br /><br />There is nothing more I love to read about than stories set in the 80’s and in my home state of California. The story has elements of magical realism, witches, a thrilling murder mystery and supernatural – which I enjoyed reading about. The story flowed well and written in a very distinct voice that I really enjoyed including diary entries. The story is about Mayhem Brayburn and her mother Roxy who leaves to Santa Maria, California, a beautiful coastal town to escape an abusive father. Moving back to their hometown, May befriends the kids adopted by her aunt where she discovers some magic and what life will look like for her in her future. <br /><br />I thought that the writing was immersive, and I did somehow get the Lost Boys feminist take of this story - a retelling of some sorts. I thought the weaving of the story line with the backstory was creatively written and well done. This was a real enjoyable read that I will continue to recommend to readers of YA and anyone looking for a great supernatural feminist read. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5777268709366640474" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


